The Embassy of Kindness (@theembassyofkindness) all started at an InstaMeet in Melbourne, Australia. Kanesan Nathan (@legojacker) and Amal Bleed (@toffyinc) led a photo walk around the city, documenting what kindness looked like with fellow, local Instagrammers. Then, they started talking to strangers. “Our very first portrait of kindness was a man called Philip. He was kind but he was skeptical about the power of kindness to change the world,” explains Kanesan. “We looked at each other and thought, ‘Challenge accepted.’” Today, through their portraiture and captions, The Embassy of Kindness seeks to exemplify how kindness can connect us all. “Any act, no matter how big or small, has the power to change a person’s life in a profound way,” says Amal. “It’s about celebrating our shared humanity.”
For this Worldwide InstaMeet (#WWIM15❤), Kanesan will lead an event from Canberra, where he now lives, at the Australian National Botanic Gardens, and Amal will host from Melbourne’s city center. Both InstaMeets encourage participants to start conversations about kindness and create portraits that have become the basis for The Embassy’s photo project.
@theembassyofkindness photos by @toffyinc and @legojacker

Toast the Eggos and turn on the Christmas lights: the cast of Netflix’s “Stranger Things” are gearing up for more adventures after their ‘80s-infused sci-fi show got renewed for a new season. Here, three cast members predict what their characters will be getting into the second time around:
@milliebobby_brown (Eleven): “I hope she moves to LA and gets a big mansion and does something great.”
@noahschnapp (Will Byers): “He’s been affected by the Upside Down because he was in there so long; I heard that he might be evil.”
@nattyiceofficial (Nancy Wheeler): “I’m really digging this Nancy-on-a-mission, trying to figure things out, being a strong, strong character and coming into her own.”
#Boomerang of @noahschnapp, @gatenm123, @milliebobby_brown, @therealcalebmclaughlin and @nattyiceofficial from their recent visit with Instagram’s New York team. Check out our story to see more of what went down.

“I am an image-maker and the director of SHOWstudio, which is a website that creates and promotes fashion film. Whether I post a picture of Kate Moss, Kanye West or the roses I grow in my garden, it puts me in direct contact with my audience. The immediacy is so refreshing; it brings me right back to the reasons I started wanting to take photographs. I love using Instagram to find exciting new talent, especially new fashion illustrators.”
—Nick Knight (@nick_knight)
“This is #whoifollow:
@dear_kukula and @raycaesar1111: Both wonderful.

@unskilledworker: She has been a great discovery and her fashion illustrations have become incredibly sought after in the very short time since she first started working with us.

@ozabu: Her illustrations are so exquisite. I always find both joy and great melancholy in her work.

@____zoe_bleu____ and @_n__arcis_s___u________s: Two friends who create the most delicate and new-looking imagery I have seen in a long time.

@reinadal: She posts both her fashion film and her illustrations. She is an exciting new talent expressing herself across different media.

@customcolorshop: Pictures of special paints for custom cars, they just always make me happy.”
Photo of @bjork for @anothermagazine by @nick_knight

“Everyone always asks me ‘what inspires you? How do you create collections for Chloé (@chloe)? What is it like to be a designer living in Paris with your family?’ So my photographs are very personal. I love that I see responses from friends and fans. There is something fantastic about the possibility to be intimate but also global. This is #whoifollow.” —Clare Waight Keller (@clarewaightkeller)
@camillebwaddington: She mixes her French and British roots with a cool, chic attitude.
@jane_how: A stylist I find quite fascinating.
@robertclarkphoto: Photos which are inspiring in color, subject and composition.
@ideabooksltd: They are just genius at finding the most brilliant books and writing about their passion for them.
@ryanmcginleystudios: He is on the cutting edge of modern art photography.
@manrepeller: Hilarious commentary on fashion and life.
@_glen_luchford: A photographer and good friend who posts hilarious images of himself.
@hughhefner: Just too fabulous.
Photo by @clarewaightkeller

“My job is to direct the fashion that you see in W Magazine (@wmag). I create ideas for stories and then work closely with photographers to make them come alive on the pages. I love to be able to communicate directly via photographs and keep a visual diary from my point of view.
This is #whoifollow:
@caitlynjenner: She is very open about her story and she is introducing everyone to a new era.
@badgalriri: Rihanna is a risk-taker with a fearless attitude.
Photographer @mertalas and designer @riccardotisci17: They are fun and represent their art, but also their love for life.
@michelleobama: Meeting her at the White House was a career high point.
@badlydrawnmodels: This account makes me laugh whilst I’m working or at the airport.
@kloss_films, my partner, and @ruenninful, our Boston terrier: ‘It’s Ru’s world and we’re all just living in it.’”
—Edward Enninful (@edward_enninful)
